scopes with single-particle sensitivity.</p></div>\n</div></section><hr class="wave">\n<div class="show-for-small-only hide-for-print"><section class="panel"><div class="link-list-item">\n<h4><a href="https://link.aps.org/doi/10.1103/PhysRevApplied.7.034026">Scanning Quantum Cryogenic Atom Microscope</a></h4>\n<p>Fan Yang, Alicia J. Koll&#225;r, Stephen F. Taylor, Richard W. Turner, and Benjamin L. Lev</p>\n<p><a href="https://link.aps.org/doi/10.1103/PhysRevApplied.7.034026">Phys. Rev. Applied <b>7</b>,  034026 (2017)</a></p>\n<p>Published March 27, 2017</p>\n</div>\n<a class="small button" href="https://physics.aps.org/featured-article-pdf/10.1103/PhysRevApplied.7.034026"> Read PDF</a></section></div>\n<section><h2>Subject Areas</h2>\n<div class="article-subject-areas">\n<a class="subject-label" href="https://physics.aps.org/browse?subject_area=atomic-molecular">Atomic and Molecular Physics</a><a class="subject-label" href="https://physics.aps.org/browse?subject_area=strongly-correlated">Strongly Correlated Materials</a>\n</div></section><section class="hide-for-print"><div class="row article-more-synopses">\n<div class="medium-6 columns"></div>\n<div class="medium-6 columns"></div>\n</div>\n<h2>Related Articles</h2>\n<section class="feed-item"><div class="feed-item-image"><a href="https://physics.aps.org/articles/v10/41"><img alt="Viewpoint: Atom Interferometers Warm Up" src="http://physics.aps.org/assets/10.1103/Physics.10.41/figure/1/thumb"></a></div>\n<div class="feed-item-details">\n<span class="feed-item-subject">Atomic and Molecular Physics</span><h3 class="feed-item-title"><a href="https://physics.aps.org/articles/v10/41">Viewpoint: Atom Interferometers Warm Up</a></h3>\n<time class="feed-item-date">April 17, 2017</time><p class="feed-item-deck">Researchers have demonstrated an atom interferometer based on a warm vapor, rather than on a cold atomic gas.<a href="https://physics.aps.org/articles/v10/41"> Read More &#187;</a></p>\n</div></section><section cla